Whenever possible, fostering positive relationships. Seeking justice.

Restored information on Integrity's use of homophobic slurs to describe its membership.  Included citation of official statement from Integrity USA president defending the use of homophobic slurs against membership.

Removed NPOV. The purpose of NPOV template is to attract editors with different viewpoints to edit articles that need additional insight, and “drive-by tagging” like is strongly discouraged. The editor who adds the tag should have discussed concerns on the talk page, pointing to specific issues that are actionable within the content policies. In the absence of such a discussion, or where it remains unclear what the NPOV violation is, the tag is inappropriate.
The content of the article on Integrity USA, specifically the content with citations, meets the wiktionary definition of “abuse.” See: https://en.m.wiktionary.org/wiki/abuse
Cleaning up language because Integrity still exists as a nonprofit.
